{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958052301/1138.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE FOUR\nRODANTHE PERSONALS\nThe Ladies Aid Society met'\nMonday at the home of Mrs. Lu\nrania Midgett, Prayer by Mrs.\nMidgett. Hostess served ice cream\nand cookies.\nMrs. Allen E. Gray left Tuesday\nto meet her husband in Groton,\nConn.\nMr. and Mrs. Stuart Daugherty\nand children, Stuart and Dorothy\nAnn, left today yfor Jacksonville,\nN. C. after visiting at Mirlo Beach\nLodge with their parents, Mr. and|\nMrs. Cecil Gibbs.\nMr. and Mrs. Kermit Scarbor\nough spent the week end here with\nMrs. Scarborough\u2019s parents, Mr.\nand Mrs. Levene W. Midgett.\nDavid B. Midgett Jr., U.S.C.G.,\nof Baltimore visited his mother,\nMrs. D. B. Midgett.\nMrs. Patsy Williams of Manteo\nand' Mrs. Minnie Gray of Kitty\nHawk visited Mr. and Mrs. Julian\nL. Gray and family and other\nfriends here Friday.\nFor your Paint and Supplies\nAlways Stop at\nFEARINGS, INC.\nWHY? We offer a complete line\nHEADQUARTERS FOR CAROLINIANS\nWHEN IN NORFOLK\nFAIRFAX HOTEL\nFIREPROOF RATES $3.50 UP\nTELEVISION RADIO AIR-CONDITIONED\nNOTICE TO BIDDERS\nFOR THE REMOVAL OF GARBAGE\nAND TRASH ON THE DARE BEACHES\nSealed bids will be received in the office of the Register\nof Deeds, as Clerk to the Board of County Commissioners of\nDare County, until 12:00 o'clock Noon on June 3, 1958 for the\nremoval of all garbage and household trash from the portion\nof the Dare Beaches described hereinafter for the period begin\nning, July I, 1958 and terminating June 30, 1959, in accordance\nwith the following\nCollections are to be made once each day, except Sun\ndays, during the period beginning July I, 1958 through Septem\nber 30, 1958 inclusive, and twice each week during the period\nfrom October I, 1958 to and including the 15th day of May,\n1959, and three times each week during the period from the\n16th day of May, 1959 to and including the 31st day of May,\n1959, and once each day, except Sundays, for the period from\nJune I, 1959 through June 30, 1959 inclusive.\nSealed bids will also be received at the same time in the\noffice of the Register of Deds as Clerk to the Board of County\nCommissioners of Dare County for the removal of all garbage\nand household trash from the aforesaid area of the Dare Beaches\nfor a period of three years beginning July I, 1958 and termi\nnating June 30, 1961 for the same annual schedule outlined\nabove.\nProspective bidders may submit bids for the one year\nperiod referred to above, or the three year period referred to\nabove, or both.\nThe general territory and area from which the aforesaid\nhousehold trash and garbage shall be removed includes all\nbouses, hotels, places ot business and restaurants lying adjacent\nto and in the vicinity of and along that section of the present\nU. S. Highway No. 158, extending from the East end of the\nCurrituck Sound Bridge to the East end of the Roanoke Sound\nBridge, the entire Southern Shores road or street leading North\nfrom U. S. Highway No. 158, that portion of the Oregon Inlet\nroad leading South from the aforesaid Highway No. 158 lying\nNorth of the Cape Hatteras National Seashore Recreational\nArea's North line, that portion of the Beach known as the Sound\nside at Nags Head and the paved road leading thereto, all of\nthe area and subdivision known as Avalon Beach or Shores, and\non both sides of any paved or stabilized road or street leading\nfrom U. S. Highway No. 158 or U. S. Highway No. 64 now in\nbeing, upon which houses have been constructed, for a distance\nnot in excess of one-half mile.\nThe contractor will be required to provide a dumping\nground or other disposal area for the aforesaid trash and gar\nbage which shall not be in violation of any health or other laws.\nThe Contractor will likewise be required to furnish trucks or\nother disposal units or equipment which are covered and en\nclosed.\nEach bid or proposal for the one year period above set\nout from July I, IYSB to June 30, 1959 inclusive shall be accom\npanied by a cash deposit or a certified check or bank draft\nmade payable to the order of Dare County drawn on some\nbank or trust company insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance\nCorporation in an amount equal to not less than five percent of\nthe proposal or bid. Each proposal or bid for the three year\nperiod beginning July I, 1958 and terminating June 30, 1961\nshall be accompanied by a cash deposit or certified check or\nbank draft maae payable to the order of Dare County drawn\non some bank or trust company insured by the Federal Deposit\nInsurance Corporation in an amount equal to at least five per\ncent of I/3 of the total amount of the proposal or bid. No pro\nposal or bid shall be accepted or considered by the said Board\nunless at the time of its filing the same shall be accompanied by\nsaid deposit or check as aforesaid. This deposit shall be retained\nby Dare County if the successful bidder fails to execute the\ncontract for the aforesaid removal of garbage and household\ntrash on or before the 20th day of June, 1958, and fails to\ngive the performance bond as provided hereinafter.\nThe successful bidder will be required to give a perform\nance bond for 100 percent of the contract price guaranteeing\nthe faithful performance of his contract. Said bond to be exe\ncuted by a surety company licensed under the laws of the State\nof North Carolina to execute such a bond.\nThe right to reject any and all bids and proposals for any\nreason whatsoever is hereby reserved\nFurther information concerning the bids and contracts may\nbe had at the office of the Register of Deeds of Dare County,\nNorth Carolina.\nThis the 15th day of May, 1958.\nMELVIN R. DANIELS, CLERK TO THE BOARD OF\nCOUNTY COMMISSIONERS OF DARE COUNTY, N. C.\nWINTER FERRY SCHEDULES\nALLIGATOR RIVER FERRY\nLv. East Lake Lv. Tyrrell County\n6:00 A M. 6:40 A M.\n7:20 A.M. 8.00 A M.\n8 40 A.M. 9:20 A.M.\n10:00 A.M. 10:40 A.M.\n11:20 A.M. 12:00 Noon\n12:40 P.M. 1:20 P.M.\n2:00 P.M. s 2:40 P.M.\n3:20 P.M. 4:00 P.M.\n4:40 P.M. 5:20 P.M.\n6:00 P.M. 6:40 P.M.\n7:20 P.M. 8:00 P.M.\nOREGON INLET FERRY\nLv. North Shore \u2019Ey. South Shore\n5:00 A.M. 5:30 A.M.\n5;30 A.M. 6 00 A.M.\n6:00 A.M. 6:30 A.M.\n6:30 A.M. 7 00 A.M.\n7:00 A.M. 7:30 A.M.\n7:30 A.M. 8 00 A.M.\n8:00 A.M. 8 30 A M.\n8:30 A M. 00 A.M.\n9:00 A.M. 9:30 A.M.\n9:30 A.M. 10:00 A.M.\n10:00 A.M. 10:30 A.M.\n10:30 A.M. \u2019J 00 A.M.\n11:00 A.M. M\n11:30 A.M. 12:00 Noon\n12:00 Noon 12:30 P.M.\n12:30 P.M. ]:00 P.M.\n1:00 P.M. 1:30 P.M.\n1:30 P.M. 2:00 P.M.\n2:00 P.M. M\n2:30 P.M. 3:00 P.M.\n3:00 P.M. 3:30 P.M.\n3:30 P.M. 4:00 P.M.\n4:00 P.M. 4:30 P.M.\n4:30 P.M, 5:00 P.M.\n5:00 P.M. 5:30 P.M.\n5:30 P.M. 00 P M\n6.00 P.M. 30 P M.\n6:30 P.M. Starts Moy 1 7:00 P.M.\nHATTERAS INLET FERRY\nLv. Hatteras Lv. Ocracoke\n7:00 A.M. 8:00 A.M.\n10:30 AM. 4 11:00 A.M.\n12:30 P.M. 1:30 P.M.\n3:00 P.M. 4:00 P.M.\nBUS SCHEDULE\nBETWEEN MANTEO\nAND HATTERAS\nEffective April 1, 1958\nNORTHBOUND\nLv. Hatteras 9:00 A.M.\nAr. Manteo 11:45 A.M.\nSOUTHBOUND\nLv. Manteo 2:45 P.M.\nAr. Hatteras 5:45 P.M,\nCHARTERED TRIPS\nHATTERAS-MANTEO\nBUS LINE\nPhone 104 Hatteras, N. C.\nSTATEMENT BY\nDAVID STICK\nFOR COUNTY COMMISSIONER\nATLANTIC TOWNSHIP\nI have filed as a candidate\nfor Commissioner from Atlantic\nTownship subject to the Demo\ncratic primary.\nI am associated with no political\nclique, nor am I bound by promises\nto any individual or special group,\nand except for my wife no one\nwas consulted concerning my de\ncision to run for this office.\nIn the event the voters of Dare\nCounty should elect me to this\nposition, I promise them simply\nthat I will not come under the\ndomination of any so-called politi\ncal leader; that I will do my best\nto approach each new problem\nwith an open mind; that I will\nmake my final decision in each\ninstance on the basis of what I\nfeel is best for the prosperity,\nprogress and well being of Dare\nCounty as a whole; that I will\nstate my position clearly on each\nissue as it arises; and that I will\nconduct my public business in pub\nlic and not behind closed doors.\nAs a resident of Dare County\nsince 1929 I have attempted to\nparticipate in civic activities when\never called on, to keep well inform\ned on county affairs, and to learn\nas much as I could about the pres\nent and future needs of the county.\nI feel that my past experience as\na reporter covering the county\ngovernment in' Manteo, the State\nCapitol in Raleigh, and the Na\ntional Capitol in Washington, and\nas a writer concentrating on the\nhistory of Dare County, would be\nuseful to a member of the Board\nof County Commissioners.\nI do not solicit the vote of any\nindividual who would expect spe\ncial consideration from me in ex\nchange for such support.\nOn the basis of the above state\nment I submit my name to the\nvoters of Dare County.\nDAVID STICK\nColington\nT-5-2-stc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of John Alford\nFarrow of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said John Alford\nFarrow to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will lie\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the sth day of May, 1958.\nALICE F. MEEKINS\nAvon, N. C.\nT-5-9-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Naomi D.\nWescott of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Naomi D. Wes\ncott to present them to the under\nsigned within one year from date\nof this notice or same will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 6th day of May, 1958.\nBROCKIIE DANIELS\nManteo, N. C.\nT-5-16-6tc\nSJ\u00a9\n-rt-s- Jaw IftL i\najfpA-\nJHggWj\nPut the low cost\nbeauty off\nCOLOR\nTELEPHONES\nin your home\nSo many folks are surprised\nwhen they find out how little\nextra telephones in color cost.\nThe beauty of fashion looks\nexpensive but it isn\u2019t.\nPlease call our business\noffice today for complete infor\nmation on color telephones.\n\nThe Norfolk Carolina\nTelephone Telegraph Co.\nManteo Elizabeth City Coinjock\nKill Devil'Hills Edenton\nTHE COASTLAND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\nHALLETT F. PERRY\nSEEKS RENOMINATION\nFOR COMMISSIONER\nI hereby announce my candidacy\nfor County Commissioner from At\nlantic Township, Dare County,\nN. C., subject to the Democrat Pri\nmary, May 31, 1958. I solicit your\nvote and support in the forthcom\ning election and if elected, promise\nto do my very best for all the\npeople of the County in all matters\ncoming before the Board for its\nconsideration. I believe I am com\npetent and capable of serving on\nhe Board of County Commission\ners, having had experience as a\nmember for several years.\nMy sole interest is to serve all\nsections of thA County to the best\nof my ability and to see that every\none gets a square deal.\nYour vote and support will be\nappreciated. I\nHALLETT F. PERRY\nKitty Hawk. N. C.\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Dennett Hen\nry Ransom of Frisco, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Dennett Henry\nRansom to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will\nbe pleaded in bar of their recovery..\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 28th day of April, 1958.\nELLA MAY RANSOM\nFrisco, N. C.\nT-5-2-6tc\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned having duly\nqualified as the administrator of\nthe Estate of Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, late of the above named\ncounty and state, all persons hav\ning claims of whatsoever nature\nagainst the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby notified to\nexhibit the said claim or claims to\nthe undersigned on or before the\n2nd day of May, 1959, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery. All persons indebt\ned to the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby requested to\npay the said indebtedness to the\nundersigned immediately.\nThis the 2nd day of May. 1958.\nFLOYD L. HOOPER\nAdministrator\nT-5-2-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nNorth Carolina\nDare County.\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntor of the estate of Barte Bar\nnette, deceased, late of Dare\nCounty, North Carolina, this is to\nnotify all persons having claims j\nagainst the estate of the said de-:\nceased to exhibit them to the un\ndersigned at Frisco, North Caro\nlina, on or before the 15th day of\nApril, 1959, or this notice will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nwill please make immediate pay\nment.\nThis 15th dnv of Anril. 1958.\nBENNIE BARNETT,\nFrisco, North Carolina\nAdministrator\nT-4-25-6tc\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nBEFORE THE BOARD OF\nCOMMISSIONERS,\nDARE COUNTY\nNOVICE OF HEARING\nON A PETITION\nFOR ABANDONMENT\nOF STREET OR WAY\nRoanoke Sound Shores, Inc,\nPetitioner\nto\nDare County, Thomas Gilliam, 111,\net als\nI All persons having or claiming\nto have any right, title or\n'in or to lands located in Nags\nHead Township, Dare County,\nI North Carolina, formerly known as\nNags Head Beach property of\nNags Head Development Corpora\ntion, as shown on Map or Plat, re\ncorded in Map Book 1, pages 192-\n189, Office of the Register of\nDeeds, Dare County. North Caro\nlina, and the Roanoke Sound\nShores Inc. property shown on\nmap or plat thereof, recorded in\nMap Book 2, Page 90, Public Reg\nistry of Dare County, North Caro\nlina, and the public will take no\ntice that a petition has been filed\nwith this Board, the purpose of\nwhich is to abandon a certain\nstreet, way or right of wav, dedi\ncated to the 'public by plat, but\nunopened, unpaved and unused,\nwhich said area is situated to the\nNorth of Block C and South of\nBlock D, and running in an East-\nWest direction, and designated on\nthe plat of Petitioner\u2019s property\nas a 10 foot Lane, a copy of said\npetition is on file with the Clerk\nto the Board of Commissioners.\nAnd all such persons will take\nnotice that a hearing upon the\nPetition will be had at the June\nMeeting of the Board of Commis\nsioners, in the Court House in\nManteo, N. C. at 10:00 A.M. on\nTuesday, June 3, 1958.\nAnd all interested parties will\nfurther take notice that the Board\nwill act on said Petition at its\nJune meeting; and that all inter\nseted parties shall attend and make\nprotest, if any they have to said\npetition, or they would be bound by\nthe action of the Board, as by law\nprovided, unless appeal is duly\nfiled before the said Board.\nNotice is hereby issued by\nauthority and at the direction of\nthe Board at its May meeting.\nThis 6th day of May, 1958.\nDARE COUNTY\nBOARD OF COMMISSIONERS\nBy Melvin R. Daniels\nClerk to the Board\nT-5-9-4te\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executor of\nthe estate of Daisy H. Midgett of\nNags Head, Dare County, North\nCarolina, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against the\nestate of said Daisy H. Midgett,\nto present them to the undersigned\nwithin one year from date of this\nnotice or same will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate please make\nimmediate payment.\nThis the 3rd day of May, 1958.\nCORNELIUS P. MIDGETT\nNags Head, N. C.\nWorth and Horner, Attorney.\nT-5-9-6tc\nNOTICE OF SALE\nBy virtue of the authority con\ntained in that certain Deed of\nTrust executed by Major M. Mor\nrisette and wife, Emma Weeks'\nMorrisette. to Southern Loan and\nInsurance Company, Trustee, dated\nMarch 2, 1953, and recorded in'\nBook 43, page 450, of the public\nregistry of Dare County, N. C., I\ndefault having been made in the\nconditions thereof; the said Trustee\u2019\nwill, on the 3rd day of June, 1958,\nat 12 o\u2019clock Noon, at the Court-]\nhouse door of Dare County, N. C.,\noffer for sale at public auction to,\nthe highest bidder for cash the\nfollowing described property:\nSituate in Atlantic Township,\nDare County, North Carolina, to\ni wit:\nAll that certain lot or parcel\nI of land, together with the houses\nI and improvements thereon. ly\ning and being near Kill Devil\nHills in Atlantic Township, Dare\nCounty, N. C., and known as,\ndesignated and being Lot No. 28,\nas shown on plat \u201cB\u201d of the sub\ndivision known as Virginia Dare\nShores. Man or plat of said plat\n\u201cB\u201d of Virginia Dare Shores\nduly recorded in Book 17, page\n105, office of the Register of\nDeeds of Dare County, N. C n\nreference to which is hereby\nmade for a more particular de\nscription thereof.\nSaid lot fronting fifty (50)\nfeet on the East side of U. S.\nHighway No. 158 sometimes\nknown as Virginia Dare Trail,\nand extending Eastwardly be\ntween parallel lines to the At\nlantic Ocean.\nSame being the lands conveyed\nto M. M. Morrisette. Jr. by Gra\nham W. Be\u2019l et ux by deed dated\nJuly 3. 1936, and duly recorded\nin Book 17, page 268, office of\nthe Register of Deeds of Dare\nCounty. N. C.\nThe above property will be sold\nsubject to taxes for the year 1958.\nA deposit of 5 per cent of the\namount bid will be required of the\nsuccessful bidder at the hour of\nsale.\nThis Notice dated and posted\nthis 3rd day of May, 1958.\nSOUTHERN LOAN\nINSURANCE COMPANY,\nTRUSTEE.\nBv Worth and Horner\nAttorneys\nT-5-9-4fn\nI Illi 111 I'- I IIIIHIIIII I II I I\nv Awwwm H B\nawa-uw J 1 1111\n1* WW ifewsijz /i\ny -7 j'.\nChoose Your Beach Site Now!\nDELRAY BEACH, KILL DEVIL HILLS, N. C.\nHere\u2019s an opportunity for you to buy the finest resort property on the\nAtlantic Coast. Just think beautiful, fully restricted, well-planned\nhomesites only 600 ft. from the surf! Delray Beach is located in the\nheart of Carolina\u2019s finest salt and fresh water fishing!\nBest of all, Delray Beach.lots are offered at sensible prices con\nvenient terms are available. Up to two years to pay.\nPrices Begin At Only\n$895.00\nFor Average 75 x 150 Site\nAlso Available: Choice ocean front lots\nand lots facing old and new U.S. #l5B.\nCHECK THESE OUTSTANDING FEATURES:\nV Fully Restricted V K\u00ab\u00aby Term* two year* to pay.\nV All lot* on Paved Street* \\J Located Within City Limit* of\nArea easily accessible via Wright _ Police Fire Protection, and full\nMemorial or William B. Umttead municipal service*.\nBridpe*.\nJACQUIN\u2019S Jg\nvrika M\nROYALE\n\u00bb2 PINT\nW1 rrnriit iwntnlnM\nOlSriUtD FROM .GRAIN 80 PROOF\nCHARLES JACRUIN et Cit, lac., Pbila., Pl,\nCheck\nThese\nFa Features!\nZ i \"Snap-On\" Handle\ni Slide chute prevents\n11 clumping\nFingertips throttle control\n1 Deflector controls\ndischarge\nx\\ Sturdy steel deck\nnKL. \u2014-S ju OWsef wheel prevents\nscalping\n___ Leaf mulcher included\nFrom $69.95 Up\nWorcester\nROTARY POWER MOWER\nThey had you in mind when they designed this all new Worces\nter Rotor Master. From the streamlined adjustable handle to the\npowerful nationally famous 4-cycle engine, everything is pro\nvided to make mowing lawns a pleasure. Tempered steel blade\ncuts tough grass and weeds; inset wheels let you trim right up\nto walls or shrubs. Precision built by Worcester for trouble-free\nservice.\nI SPECIAL MOWER TRADE\nFROM NOW UNTIL MAY 30th, WE WILL GIVE YOU\nA TRADE-IN ALLOWANCE FOR YOUR OLD MOWER, S\nEITHER POWER OR HAND TYPE, REGARDLESS OF\nCONDITION. SEE US TODAY.\nPOWFUL ELECTRIC MOWERS ALSO AVAILABLE\nMANTEO FURNITURE CO.\nOPPOSITE POST OFFICE\nPHONE 51-J MANTEO, N. C.\nFRIDAY, MAY 23, 1958","height":"25688","width":"18449"}}
